<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-16T10:07:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-16T10:07:00-05:00" n="457" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2327¾: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The German Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-16T10:07:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 16, 1915—10:07 a. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:15 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your letter followed me here where I have urgent business for a day. I am
                            sending one more wireless to Berlin. It is really not our fault if the
                            events of the last weeks postponed a solution of the older question.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. Bernstorff</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>